      "author": "jv209",
      "description": "Removed the smooth collapse transitions feature which was indistinguishable from Obsidian's native behavior. Also includes the v0.7.2 changes: redesigned settings tabs with icons, title overrides in their own tab, default collapse state settings, copy button relocated to bottom-right of callout body, and drop shadow removal.",
      "downloadCount": 0,
      "draft": false,
      "name": "v0.7.3 — Remove smooth transitions",
      "prerelease": true,
      "publishedAt": "2026-02-23T03:02:52Z",
      "tag": "v0.7.3"
    },
    {
      "assets": [],
      "author": "jv209",
      "description": "Redesigned the settings tab bar with icon-only inactive tabs and a sliding label animation. Title overrides now live in their own tab with a grid layout matching the detection and custom callout sections. Added separate default collapse state settings for the full modal and quick pick. Removed the drop shadow feature. Fixed smooth collapse transitions which were invisible due to a CSS conflict with Obsidian. Moved the copy button from the callout title bar to the bottom-right of the callout body to avoid overlapping with Obsidian's native edit button.",
      "downloadCount": 0,
      "draft": false,
      "name": "v0.7.2 — Settings overhaul and collapse defaults",
      "prerelease": true,
      "publishedAt": "2026-02-23T02:33:29Z",
